          "old_hash_id": "scientists-reveal-how-an-all-female-fish-has-cloned-itself-for-years-1773496858254",
          "hash_id": "r29jgxwu-1",
          "author_name": "Mini Tiwari",
          "content": "Scientists revealed how Amazon Molly, an asexual all-female species of fish, has been cloning itself for years. As per evolutionary theory, a species needs to have some sexual activity to keep genes diverse. However, the secret behind Amazon Molly's existence is gene conversion, which works by replacing a segment of chromosomal DNA with a corresponding sequence copied from another chromosome. ",
