          "content": "Oscar statuettes cost about $400 (₹36,960) to produce but are officially valued at just $1. Since 1951, Oscar winners must sign an agreement stating they cannot sell trophy without first offering it back to Academy of Motion Picture Arts & Sciences for $1. The rule was introduced to preserve award's prestige and prevent it from becoming a mere collector's item.",
